abstract: Michael Avenatti, the combative lawyer who gained fame by representing porn star Stormy Daniels in lawsuits involving President Donald Trump, was convicted Friday of trying to extort sportswear giant Nike.
snippet: Michael Avenatti, the combative lawyer who gained fame by representing porn star Stormy Daniels in lawsuits involving President Donald Trump, was convicted Friday of trying to extort sportswear giant Nike.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Avenatti, the combative lawyer who gained fame by representing porn star Stormy Daniels in lawsuits involving President Donald Trump, was convicted Friday of trying to extort sportswear giant Nike.
headline_main: Michael Avenatti Is Convicted of Trying to Extort Nike
headline_print_headline: Michael Avenatti Is Convicted of Trying to Extort Nike

abstract: U.S. Army Secretary Ryan McCarthy said on Friday there were no investigations into Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman, the former National Security Council aide who testified in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial and was fired by the White House along with his twin brother.
snippet: U.S. Army Secretary Ryan McCarthy said on Friday there were no investigations into Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman, the former National Security Council aide who testified in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial and was fired by the Whi...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Army Secretary Ryan McCarthy said on Friday there were no investigations into Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman, the former National Security Council aide who testified in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial and was fired by the White House along with his twin brother.
headline_main: No Investigations of Ousted White House Aide Vindman: U.S. Army Secretary
headline_print_headline: No Investigations of Ousted White House Aide Vindman: U.S. Army Secretary

abstract: A U.S. jury on Friday found Michael Avenatti guilty in a criminal trial accusing the celebrity lawyer of trying to extort Nike Inc out of millions of dollars and defraud a youth basketball coach he represented.
snippet: A U.S. jury on Friday found Michael Avenatti guilty in a criminal trial accusing the celebrity lawyer of trying to extort Nike Inc out of millions of dollars and defraud a youth basketball coach he represented.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A U.S. jury on Friday found Michael Avenatti guilty in a criminal trial accusing the celebrity lawyer of trying to extort Nike Inc out of millions of dollars and defraud a youth basketball coach he represented.
headline_main: Celebrity Lawyer Michael Avenatti Is Found Guilty in Nike Extortion Case
headline_print_headline: Celebrity Lawyer Michael Avenatti Is Found Guilty in Nike Extortion Case

abstract: The mayor of Tel Aviv ordered the removal on Friday of highway billboards that appeared to call for the surrender at gunpoint of Palestinian leaders for the sake of peace.
snippet: The mayor of Tel Aviv ordered the removal on Friday of highway billboards that appeared to call for the surrender at gunpoint of Palestinian leaders for the sake of peace.
lead_paragraph: TEL AVIV — The mayor of Tel Aviv ordered the removal on Friday of highway billboards that appeared to call for the surrender at gunpoint of Palestinian leaders for the sake of peace.
headline_main: Israeli Mayor Orders Palestinian 'Surrender' Billboards Removed
headline_print_headline: Israeli Mayor Orders Palestinian 'Surrender' Billboards Removed

abstract: The U.S. killing of a top Iranian general was a miscalculation that has had the effect of bolstering support in Iraq for the removal of American troops, a longtime goal of Tehran, Iran's foreign minister said Friday.
snippet: The U.S. killing of a top Iranian general was a miscalculation that has had the effect of bolstering support in Iraq for the removal of American troops, a longtime goal of Tehran, Iran's foreign minister said Friday.
lead_paragraph: MUNICH — The U.S. killing of a top Iranian general was a miscalculation that has had the effect of bolstering support in Iraq for the removal of American troops, a longtime goal of Tehran, Iran's foreign minister said Friday.
headline_main: Iran: US Killing of General Was a Miscalculation
headline_print_headline: Iran: US Killing of General Was a Miscalculation

abstract: The public struggles of White House adviser Kellyanne Conway and her husband, George T. Conway III, are not shtick, friends say, and they are not having fun.
snippet: The public struggles of White House adviser Kellyanne Conway and her husband, George T. Conway III, are not shtick, friends say, and they are not having fun.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — George T. Conway III has described the work of his wife, Kellyanne Conway, for President Trump in terms usually reserved for hostage situations: brainwashed by a cult, suffering from Stockholm syndrome, an overwhelmed mother protecting a destructive man-child.

abstract: A Chinese woman convicted of resisting arrest after she was chased from President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort was sentenced Friday to six months in jail.
snippet: A Chinese woman convicted of resisting arrest after she was chased from President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort was sentenced Friday to six months in jail.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — A Chinese woman convicted of resisting arrest after she was chased from President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort was sentenced Friday to six months in jail.
headline_main: Chinese Woman Who Fled Mar-a-Lago Gets 6 Months
headline_print_headline: Chinese Woman Who Fled Mar-a-Lago Gets 6 Months

abstract: Agents from a special tactical team that normally confronts smugglers on the border are being sent to sanctuary cities across the country.
snippet: Agents from a special tactical team that normally confronts smugglers on the border are being sent to sanctuary cities across the country.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration is deploying law enforcement tactical units from the southern border as part of a supercharged arrest operation in sanctuary cities across the country, an escalation in the president’s battle against localities that refuse to participate in immigration enforcement.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump contended this week that the United States saved the entire Philippines from Islamic State terrorism. His assertion vastly overstated both the threat IS posed to the country and what the U.S. did about it.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump contended this week that the United States saved the entire Philippines from Islamic State terrorism. His assertion vastly overstated both the threat IS posed to the country and what the U.S. did about it.
lead_paragraph: MANILA, Philippines — U.S. President Donald Trump contended this week that the United States saved the entire Philippines from Islamic State terrorism. His assertion vastly overstated both the threat IS posed to the country and what the U.S. did about it.
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump Didn't Save the Philippines from IS
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump Didn't Save the Philippines from IS
